data.title: Played Stella Kowalski from Tennessee Williams’ A Streetcar Named Desire. One of the most critically acclaimed plays of the twentieth...
data.meta_description:
268 likes, 0 comments - meryllsoriano on August 26, 2023: "Played Stella Kowalski from Tennessee Williams’ A Streetcar Named Desire. One of the most critically acclaimed plays of the twentieth century. 

It was an amazing and scary experience.

Theatre is so different from film and TV. Every time we’re about to go on stage, I felt so weak and want to hurl. The anxiety, the excitement. What a feeling!

It also gave a sense and understanding on having a family with your co-actors, director and the whole team that supported me and had my back,

I was scared of the big stage. Feeling naked and vulnerable. I wasn’t ready for it. But, I did it and I am proud of being a part of an important piece.

#astreetcarnameddesire #theatre".
